        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <figure id="id3293991">
      <media id="id5832463" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics15-92a5.png" mime-type="image/png" height="92" width="272"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id7015291">As with CT systems, steady state occurs if z is in the ROC of 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( z \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> . Under those conditions,</para>
    <para id="id4274578">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>X</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mover>
                    <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:mover>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>z</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>z</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{y \[ n \] =X {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( z \) z rSup { size 8{n} } } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id6579983">2/ The z-plane</para>
    <para id="id8397409">Consider a causal, stable system with pole-zero diagram shown below</para>
    <figure id="id7793172">
      <media id="id1170211343503" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics16-3375.png" mime-type="image/png" height="227" width="234"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id2962784">For z in the shaded region, the response to 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>Xz</m:mtext><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x \[ n \] = ital "Xz" rSup { size 8{n} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the steady-state response .</para>
    <para id="id7353863">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                      <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:msup>
                            <m:mtext>Yz</m:mtext>
                            <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mstyle>
                          </m:msup>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>X</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mover>
                    <m:mi>H</m:mi>
