          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{y \[ n \] = ital "Yz" rSup { size 8{n} } =X {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( z \) z rSup { size 8{n} } } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id10492697">3/ Sinusoidal steady-state response and DT frequency response</para>
    <para id="id4475332">a/ DT sinusoids</para>
    <para id="id9793664">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mtext>cos</m:mtext>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mtext>πϕ</m:mtext>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mstyle>
                  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x \[ n \] ="cos" \( 2 ital "πϕ"n \) } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id2832131">Listen to sinusoidal sounds with MATLAB.</para>
    <figure id="id10174254">
      <media id="id8028892" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics17-634c.png" mime-type="image/png" height="251" width="380"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id3545077">b/ Relation of frequency response to system function</para>
    <figure id="id9982048">
      <media id="id6576747" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics18-ad1e.png" mime-type="image/png" height="233" width="452"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id10351633">c/ Vectorial interpretation</para>
    <para id="id4460287">The frequency response is 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( z \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> for 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{z=e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> or 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> where 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the DT radian frequency, i.e., evaluated on the unit circle.</para>
    <figure id="id6719739">
      <media id="id1170210945507" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics19-fda8.png" mime-type="image/png" height="213" width="239"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id3025222">The radian frequency is the angle that the unit vector makes with the real axis.
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> can be evaluated vectorially by computing pole and zero vectors.</para>
    <para id="id9979827">d/ DT radian frequency and DT frequency</para>
    <list id="id10519105" list-type="bulleted">
      <item><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the radian frequency in units of radians/sample. </item>
    </list>
    <list id="id4072782" list-type="bulleted">
      <item><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> can be expressed as 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>πϕ</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ %OMEGA =2 ital "πϕ"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</item>
    </list>
    <list id="id9383178" list-type="bulleted">
      <item><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>ϕ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ϕ} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the frequency in units of cyles/sample.</item>
    </list>
    <list id="id4825651" list-type="bulleted">
      <item>The frequency response 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi fontstyle="italic">j2</m:mi><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>πϕ</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j2 ital "πϕ"} }  \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is often plotted versus 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>ϕ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ϕ} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</item>
    </list>
    <para id="id7305958">e/ Properties of 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> — periodicity</para>
    <para id="id10503578">Note</para>
    <para id="id10503582">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mover>
                    <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:mover>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                            <m:mn>2π</m:mn>
                          </m:mrow>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mover>
                      <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                      <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:mover>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi fontstyle="italic">j2π</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mover>
                      <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                      <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:mover>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j \(  %OMEGA +2π \) } }  \) = {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } } e rSup { size 8{j2π \) } }  \) = {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id3490117">which shows that the DT frequency response is periodic with period 2π. This is evident from the vector diagram.</para>
    <figure id="id10245362">
      <media id="id1170211652488" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics20-609b.png" mime-type="image/png" height="215" width="229"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id3786347">Therefore, it is only necessary to plot the DT frequency response over 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mn>2π</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{2π} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> radians.</para>
    <para id="id3056411">f/ Properties of 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> — symmetry</para>
    <para id="id8957406">For a DT LTI system, if the input 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mi>δ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x \[ n \] =δ \[ n \] } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> then the output is the unit sample response which we designate h[n]. In the Z-transform domain, 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {X}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( z \) =1} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> , and </para>
    <para id="id4537487">Thus,</para>
    <para id="id4513900">which evaluated on the unit circle is</para>
    <para id="id4513904">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mover>
                    <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:mover>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:munderover>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">∑</m:mo>
                        <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                                <m:mo stretchy="false">∞</m:mo>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mrow>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mstyle>
                        <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">∞</m:mo>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mstyle>
                      </m:munderover>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
                        <m:msup>
                          <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                          <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mrow>
                                  <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                                  <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                                </m:mrow>
                                <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                                <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mrow>
                          </m:mstyle>
                        </m:msup>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) = Sum cSub { size 8{n= -  infinity } }  cSup { size 8{ infinity } }  {h \[ n \] e rSup { size 8{ - j %OMEGA n} } } } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id3846340">We assume that h[n] is a real sequence. Then we expand the exponential</para>
    <para id="id7605162">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mover>
                    <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:mover>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:munderover>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">∑</m:mo>
                        <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                                <m:mo stretchy="false">∞</m:mo>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mrow>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mstyle>
                        <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">∞</m:mo>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mstyle>
                      </m:munderover>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mtext>cos</m:mtext>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>sin</m:mtext>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) = Sum cSub { size 8{n= -  infinity } }  cSup { size 8{ infinity } }  {h \[ n \]  \( "cos" \(  %OMEGA n \)  - j"sin" \(  %OMEGA n \)  \) } } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id4550292">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mover>
                    <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:mover>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mover>
                        <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                        <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mstyle>
                      </m:mover>
                      <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>r</m:mi>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:msub>
                    <m:mover>
                      <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                      <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mtext>~</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:mover>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msub>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mi>j</m:mi>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) = {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  rSub { size 8{r} }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) +j {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  rSub { size 8{i} }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id8138984">Therefore, 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> can be expanded into its real and imaginary parts and the magnitude computed as follows.</para>
    <para id="id6040058"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mover><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:munderover><m:mo stretchy="false">∑</m:mo><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">∞</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">∞</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:munderover><m:mrow><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mtext>cos</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {H}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  rSub { size 8{r} }  \( e rSup { size 8{j %OMEGA } }  \) = Sum cSub { size 8{n= -  infinity } }  cSup { size 8{ infinity } }  {h \[ n \] "cos" \(  %OMEGA n \) } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> even function of 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>,</para>
